We had verified the said details as informed by the management. It is the primary responsibility of the Management of MANAV INFRASTRUCTURE PVT LTD to prepare, produce and maintain all accounting and other relevant supporting records and documents required for the purpose of this certificate. This responsibility includes the design, implementation and maintenance of necessary and appropriate internal control commensurate with the nature and size of entity.
2. The above figures are verified based on the ledger balances shown in trial balance produce before us on an even date.
3. The project is under rehabilitation scheme and at the time of Project registration all required information and details of the project are duly submitted to the RERA authority. Further, while submitting registration form-3 (CA Certificate) the information in Sr.1 -f, we have ?Tick Mark? the option of rehabilitation scheme and filed relevant amounts in Sr.1 -f (i) and (iii). However, at the time of Q-1 filing, the option available in Sr.1 -f to tick rehabilitation scheme is disabled. Hence, we are not able to fill relevant amounts in Sr.1 -f (i) and (iii) in it. 
4. Breakup of the Land Cost: As per original project registration details submitted to the RERA, the total Land Cost is Rs. 51,33,96,380.00 which is consisting of (i) Stamp Duty Rs. 60,000.00 (ii) Cost of Construction of SRS Building Rs. 48,21,36,380.00 (iii) Cost of Rent paid to slum dwellers Rs.  3,12,00,000.00.
5. Breakup of the Development Cost: As per original project registration details submitted to the RERA, the total Development Cost is Rs. 99,08,37,524.00 which is consisting of (i) Cost of Construction Rs. 79,97,63,620.00 (ii) On Site Exp.
6. Loan Taken Rs.75.00 Crores, due to COVID 19 situation, Bank has capitalized interest and converted into principal amount and revised repayment schedule. Also company has took ECLGS 2.0 of INR 12.00 Crore and FITL from March 2020 to Aug 2020 was INR 3.0 Crore Hence, loan disbursement amount taken as Rs.90.00 Crores to match situation.
